The paper deals with a Bayesian algorithm for noisy sparse recovery, which involves signal processing, information theory, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of nonparametric belief propagation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions linear MMSE, which is a technique used in statistical signal processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a low-computational algorithm, which involves numerical analysis (cs.NA).
